"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-lifestyle-celeb-news-local-celebs-anele-mdoda-paris-olympics-costs-bill-gayton-mckenzie\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbLifestyle\\u00bbCeleb News\\u00bbLocal Celebs\\u00bb'Dude, you do not work for Twitter': Anele criticises Gayton McKenzie  Radio personality Anele Mdoda has advised Sport, Arts and Culture Minister Gayton McKenzie to limit his Twitter usage.  947 radio personality Anele Mdoda tells Minister Gayton McKenzie to limit his engagement on Twitter.  \\\"Dude. Stop answering. You do not work for twitter,\\\" she writes.  Themedia personalityAnele Mdoda wasreplyingto McKenzie's post about his trip to the 2024 Olympics in France, which cost taxpayers over R800,000.  \\\"I attended six meetings in Paris before the start of the Olympics. I went to the athletic villa to greet our athletes, I attended opening ceremony and watch the hockey, gymnastic & sevens game. I opened Ekhaya village & watched the rest of the Olympic Games on TV. What joyride?\\\" writes McKenzie.  The Citizenreveals that theministerrecently revealed in a parliamentary reply that his department incurred a total cost of\\u00a0R804,597.71 for his trip to Paris.  It is revealed that his flights cost R215 976.36, accommodation was R113 271 while transport was\\u00a0R454 005.  R592.63 was paid by the department for insurance. McKenzie's subsistence and travel allowance was\\u00a0R20 745.72.  South Africans took to Anele's post to call out the media personality for the way she addressed McKenzie.  Social media user @Oracle5152 writes: \\\"Calling a minister \\\"Dude\\\" is crazy.\\\"  @ChefIrma: \\\"But he does work for us, the South African public. He was attacked on X and he's answering here. I see no problem.\\\"  @ratshivhadelo: \\\"Do you know character assassination? Many people fall because they were silent when media houses were writing wrong things about them.\\\"  @Bra_Sporo: \\\"Yeeer sies very disrespectful. 'Dude' tomorrow someone call you gap. Nywe Nywe Nywe block here and there with noise.\\\"  @t_junction1: \\\"Anele, stop replying. You are also not working for Twitter.\\\"  @NombuleloPS: \\\"You are very disrespectful. We appreciate him and his updates here on twitter. Get a life!\\\"  @JoyLethabo8: \\\"Long before GNU @GaytonMcK was always engaging South Africans on Twitter. Why must that change when propaganda is spread!\\\"  What do you think of Anele's criticism?  Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below or by emailing\\u00a0info@thesouthafrican.com. You can also send a WhatsApp to\\u00a0060 011 0211. Do not forget to follow\\u00a0@TheSAnews\\u00a0on X and\\u00a0The South African\\u00a0on Facebook for the latest social media updates.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"